MonitoringLocationName: 40 m West of Well COLO_GWGS3 (in manhole)
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Well is located in a manhole 40 m west of well COLO_GWGS3 which is located across Colonial Parkway from the Gospel Spreading Farm barn. This station is located on the Hog Island VA 7.5' U.S.G.S. quadrangle. The data were collected as part of a project entitled: Determination of Ground Water Quality in Colonial National Historical Park Virginia at Locations Proximal to Urban and Agricultural Land Uses.  The data were collected and analyzed by Dr. William MacIntrye of the VA Institute of Marine Science (VIMS) Gloucester Pt. VA 23062 (tel. 804-642-7253).  The contact at Colonial National Historical Park is Chuck Rafkind - Natural Resource Manager P.O. Box 210 Yorktown VA 23690 (tel. 757-898-8677). The data were processed and uploaded to STORET by Dean Tucker NPS Water Resources Division; 1201 Oak Ridge Dr. Suite 250; Fort Collins CO 80525 (tel. 970-225-3516).***     Legacy STORET Station Type: /TYPA/AMBNT/WELL
